date_cols = ['POSTING DATE', 'EFFECTIVE DATE', 'CREATE DATE','SO Creation Date', 'SO Due Date']

    if c in df.columns:
        df[c] = pd.to_datetime(df[c],errors='coerce')

Feature Engineering(Dates)¶

In [77]:
for c in date_cols:
    if c in df.columns:
        df[f'{c}_year'] = df[c].dt.year
        df[f'{c}_month'] = df[c].dt.month
        df[f'{c}_day'] = df[c].dt.day
        df[f'{c}_weekday'] = df[c].dt.dayofweek
In [78]:
# Create a delivery delay column if we have due date and posting date
if 'SO Due Date' in df.columns and 'POSTING DATE' in df.columns:
     df['DeliveryDelay_days'] = (df['POSTING DATE'] - df['SO Due Date']).dt.days
     # Replace inf/nan
     df['DeliveryDelay_days'] = df['DeliveryDelay_days'].fillna(0)

Outlier Treatment¶

In [ ]:
#Outlier detection by Inter Quartile Range Method
In [9]:
def wisker(col):
    q1,q3=np.percentile(col,[25,75])
    iqr=q3-q1
    lw=q1-1.5*iqr
    uw=q3+1.5*iqr
    return lw,uw
In [10]:
wisker(df['LeadTime_days'])
Out[10]:
(0.0, 0.0)
In [11]:
wisker(df['LineValue'])
Out[11]:
(-224080.0, 1162800.0)
In [12]:
wisker(df['QUANTITY'])
Out[12]:
(312.0, 312.0)
In [13]:
for i in ['LeadTime_days','LineValue','QUANTITY']:
    lw,uw=wisker(df[i])
    df[i]=np.where(df[i]<lw,lw,df[i])
    df[i]=np.where(df[i]>uw,uw,df[i])

Conclusion¶

In [ ]:
The exploratory data analysis reveals that the majority of sales
come from Wooden Pallet products and that customer transport
generates the highest revenue among transporters. The warehouse 
“Company India Kanera” is the top-performing location. 
The data also shows peak sales activity around March 27, 2021.
These insights can help focus optimization efforts on 
high-performing categories and periods.
